<a name="whatis">&nbsp;</a>
<h2>
    What is TextMe?
    <a href="{$T_TEXTME_BASEURL}&cat=help#index">
        <img src="{$T_TEXTME_BASELINK}assets/images/16/arrow_up_blue.png" alt="Back to index" title="Back to index" />
    </a>
</h2>

<p>TextMe is a module for sending sms alerts.</p>
<p>TextMe gives the ability to professors to send sms alerts to lessons's participants.<br/></p>

<a name="inbox">&nbsp;</a>
<h2>
    Inbox
    <a href="{$T_TEXTME_BASEURL}&cat=help#index">
        <img src="{$T_TEXTME_BASELINK}assets/images/16/arrow_up_blue.png" alt="Back to index" title="Back to index" />
    </a>
</h2>

<p>
    You can view messages sent to you or by you in your Inbox.<br/>
    Messages sent to users that have not subscribed to TextMe sms alerts will<br/>
    still be able to see those messages in their Inbox.
</p>

<a name="inbox_compose">&nbsp;</a>
<h3>
    Compose message
    <a href="{$T_TEXTME_BASEURL}&cat=help#index">
        <img src="{$T_TEXTME_BASELINK}assets/images/16/arrow_up_blue.png" alt="Back to index" title="Back to index" />
    </a>
</h3>

<p>
    All professors of a lesson can compose messages.<br/>
    All messages composed will be visible in their recipients Inboxes.<br/>
    For those recipients who have subscribed to sms alerts an sms with the<br/>
    composes message will also be sent to their mobiles.
</p>

<ol>
    <li>Click on "Inbox" tab</li>
    <li>Click on "Compose message" link</li>
    <li>
        Select recipients.<br/>
        You can either select the predefined recipients groups (Everyone, Professors only, Students only)<br/>
        or select individual recipients and custom groups. Note that even if you don't select yourself as<br/>
        a recipient of a message TextMe will always include youself in the recipients list.<br/>
        <br/>
    </li>
    <li>Enter the message</li>
    <li>Select the date that the message will be sent. (This option is not always available. Contact your admin.)</li>
    <li>Click on "Submit" button</li>
</ol>

<p>
    Please bear in mind that TextMe uses a credit system.<br/>
    Each message has a cost depending of the sms that will be sent.<br/>
    The administrator of eFront manages how many credits a lesson can spend.<br/>
    If you are short on credits you should contact your administrator for more.
</p>

<a name="inbox_view">&nbsp;</a>
<h3>
    View message
    <a href="{$T_TEXTME_BASEURL}&cat=help#index">
        <img src="{$T_TEXTME_BASELINK}assets/images/16/arrow_up_blue.png" alt="Back to index" title="Back to index" />
    </a>
</h3>

<ol>
    <li>Click on "Inbox" tab</li>
    <li>Click on a message</li>
</ol>

<p>
    Professors of a lesson will also view the recipients of the message.<br/>
    For each recipient they will be able to see the status of the sms (delivered, pending or failed)<br/>
    as well as if they have read the message locally.
</p>

