<a name="configuration">&nbsp;</a>
<h2>
    Configure
    <a href="{$T_TEXTME_BASEURL}&cat=help#index">
        <img src="{$T_TEXTME_BASELINK}assets/images/16/arrow_up_blue.png" alt="Back to index" title="Back to index" />
    </a>
</h2>

<p>
    The "Sender ID" is a word that appears as the sender of the sms alerts.<br/>
    Every time that an sms alert is being send from a lesson account all recipients<br/>
    will see as that word as the sender of the alert.The default "Sender ID" is eFront.<br/>
    <br/>
    It is encouraged to give a unique "Sender ID" for each lesson. This will help users<br/>
    that have subscribed for sms alerts to more than one lessons distinguish between alerts<br/>
</p>

<ol>
    <li>
        Enter the new "Sender ID".
        <br/>A "Sender ID" must always start with a character in latin.
        <br/>It can consist of up to 11 latin characters in capital or digits.
    </li>
    <li>
        Click on "Submit" button.
    </li>
</ol>

<a name="subscribe">&nbsp;</a>
<h2>
    Subscribe
    <a href="{$T_TEXTME_BASEURL}&cat=help#index">
        <img src="{$T_TEXTME_BASELINK}assets/images/16/arrow_up_blue.png" alt="Back to index" title="Back to index" />
    </a>
</h2>

<p>
    Subscription to TextMe sms alerts is done in three steps.
</p>

<ol>
    <li>
        Enter your mobile number.<br/>
        Mobile numbers should be prefixed with the international calling code of your country.<br/>
        e.g If you use the services of a Greek mobile operator then you should the internatinal<br/>
        calling code of Greece which is 30. Let's assume that your mobile number is 690123456xx.<br/>
        You should then enter 30690123456xx.
    </li>
    <li>
        Enter the verification code.<br/>
        After entering your mobile number an sms with a verification code will be sent to you.<br/>
        This is done to verify that you are the owner of the provided mobile number.<br/>
        Enter the code to the subscription form.
    </li>
    <li>
        Select the lessons from which you wish to receive sms alerts.<br/>
        You can activate/deactivate sms alerts for a lesson at anytime.
    </li>
</ol>
